On #GivingTuesday, the President of the United States encourages people to participate in acts of charity and kindness. He mentions the devastating impact of Hurricanes Harvey, Irma, and Maria, as well as wildfires in California, and urges Americans to continue supporting those affected by these disasters. The President emphasizes the resilience of the American people and highlights the importance of unity, compassion, and giving in overcoming challenges. He expresses gratitude to those who have already contributed to charitable organizations and encourages everyone to continue helping those in need, particularly those affected by recent natural disasters.